emails.content:
To view this email as a web page, go to the following address: https://pages.awscloud.com/index.php/email/emailWebview?mkt_tok=MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNa-MvtXSnb51RYtWWUoOA-GBem6P400t81Zw6iMIAvN-l7bDvlAq0ExZSP51iPGdguVngtq2LmzM2VL9qWG4eigTQDL7DjOSmFQCa5QweIoyAQETc7d3ymQ&tkn_set=7goOJ6CUdWJcoW5StqXIe%2Fi6x1mkB%2FDQ38safpmWtqNcpSYMG4WqSQ%3D%3D

AI Conclave
Online

Thursday, 30 January, 2025
Online

<https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNa-Mvf77meAPY4MAYrL-69uPcN0aFvLqK_N4dWI9y68XCr-iO7m48sV_iKtf_dlsBuYB4kI=>

================================

Last chance to register!

Fuel innovation with data and generative AI

You're invited to the 8th edition of AWS AI Conclave Online on 30 January, 2025, where AWS leaders will unveil the transformative possibilities of generative AI, data and cloud computing.

 Join us for an immersive experience featuring keynote sessions with AWS and industry experts, who will guide you through technical deep-dives into cutting-edge generative AI and data solutions. Discover data-driven innovation strategies, practical solutions for accelerating development cycles, and real-world applications that can transform your business. 

 Whether you're a developer, business executive, startup founder, seasoned entrepreneur, or tech enthusiast, this event offers valuable insights to help you create intelligent next-gen applications, enhance customer experiences, unlock new revenue streams, and scale your AI and data initiatives effectively.

Seats are filling quickly! Don't miss this opportunity to be at the forefront of the AI revolution. Register now to secure your spot at this transformative event.

----------------------------------

Learn more 
<https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNa-Mvf77meAPY4MAYrL-69uPcN0aFvLqK_N4dWI9y68XCr-iO7m48sV_iKtf_dlsBuYB4kI=>

----------------------------------

Featured Speakers

Rick Sears
Director, Data Processing & Experience
 AWS

Luke Anderson
Managing Director, Generative AI, Machine Learning & Data, APJ
 AWS

 Sundar VG 
 Director, India Specialist
 AWS

Vasant Rao
Managing Director
IDC India

Harsha Bhogle
Indian cricket commentator and journalist

Ravichandran Ashwin
Indian cricketer

----------------------------------

Register now 
<https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNa-Mvf77meAPY4MAYrL-69uPcN0aFvLqK_N4dWI9y68XCr-iO7m48sV_iKtf_dlsBuYB4kI=>

----------------------------------

What's on at AWS AI Conclave Online?


Generative AI and data
Discover the potential of generative AI and data, showcasing the power of the most transformational technologies of our time. Learn how you can AWS to fuel innovation with data and generative AI.


Keynote and 15+ sessions
Attend the live keynotes and breakout sessions presented by industry and technology leaders, technical deep-dive sessions on generative AI & data foundations, and more.


Interact with AWS experts
Participate in the live Q&A with AWS experts to gain a deeper understanding of AWSâ€™ solutions.


Get a certificate of attendance
Attend 5 or more live sessions on the day of the event to get a certificate of attendance.



----------------------------------

Register now 
<https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNa-Mvf77meAPY4MAYrL-69uPcN0aFvLqK_N4dWI9y68XCr-iO7m48sV_iKtf_dlsBuYB4kI=>

----------------------------------

emails.subject: Fwd: Register for a call back
emails.content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: John Fernandes <john@riverdalecloud.com.au>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2025 at 06:05
Subject: Fwd: Register for a call back
To: John <john@riverdalecloud.com>



-------- Original Message --------
Subject: Register for a call back
Date: 2025-01-22 11:03
From: Nathan Lee <john@cloudriverdale.com.au>
To: john@cloudriverdale.com.au
Reply-To: nathan.lee@employmenthero.com


From: Nathan Lee <nathan.lee@employmenthero.com>

Name: Nathan Lee
Email: nathan.lee@employmenthero.com
Contact Number: 02 7254 5395
Message: Hi Cloud Riverdale,   Nathan here from the Partnerships team at
Employment Hero, hope you've had a great start to 2025!   Saw you offered
IT consulting services, and was wondering if your clients ask you for HR or
payroll software recommendations?  If so, we've introduced a Referral
Partner Program, allowing you to earn commissions for successful referrals.

Get ahead of upcoming tax changes

Understanding your tax obligations can be difficult, especially as your
business expands and tax rules and rates change.

Our latest report outlines key tax trends and changes to be aware of
heading into 2025, so you can help your business stay compliant and
continue to grow.



Learn about:

emails.content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: W F <wnaz0410@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2025 at 07:44
Subject: Fwd: Tools and Incentives to grow your business
To: John <john@riverdalecloud.com.au>



---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: NSW Government <businessnews@comms.service.nsw.gov.au>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2025, 1:03 pm
Subject: Tools and Incentives to grow your business
To: <wnaz0410@gmail.com>


Nominate a great trainee or apprentice
View in Browser >
<https://view.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=b9a453065610defaaad6ca4ead9d90aca02c04944c26ebf838e47895ad31533e173ef4d50715920ceaaaf6fb4ac6df179953a2c126b2e38c75867bdbc0a13e7eec003831fb7834176633eecb3eb51085>
[image: NSW Government]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e50bfccd93d04212eb95e6d334ff53b8ca8add4cd9a5d4e66a8a6756277615219b128f604c47926c687f14771d0b0c7bf11b663cfd3385a515>
[image: Replace old business equipment and save]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e55e099d3d915f98cfb42ae0db17c70c88660532cd7035311640568d27f84931f17cc6ad5907def039a6de4e154690d377cef35813afcc75a5>
Hello Wilma
*Set yourself up for success* this new year. *The NSW Government* has
multiple programs designed to help you expand and grow your business in
2025, including:

   1. Financial incentives
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5db1259653653afbdfa482a3f35faaee0a0857d011962787086305db9dd54abb4bd4e2b464907604ad5794784d31a32654a11c388b2188ab5>
   to hire an apprentice or a trainee.
   2. Help to set your business up to export
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e509bb9dd0d4bf6c5f9bd1147acbc7ed1c3838dc3cc5c80ab8022e46b75cbcda07c637fdd12378b8552bd33ab88d06aea8b01aff12179a2bac>
   products and services internationally
   3. Fee-free short courses
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e58e64e773d171d42a24a076b7073bd23083298f582b63df6293f87ce66d5d802bcaad4dfeee0a2c65384efed08cdeb4c0df5b03ab3cf6936d>
   in digital
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e528b89360b55ba34f75c116a27c3cda143740d5439083e8dc54e5b0e3e21d612bf455ad53aa90ca8a93670506a756b305e03584399edcfa90>
or
   construction
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5b4f87726872fe6fac8a37d90b8ba8f03663b291d8d56e07eeb6f32f848d90db4f7b5e47e4e5e8dc01bdce8dba3c1c788a98417f7bb030feb>
   .
   4. Free local, independent advisory sessions
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5ae58191752e709673e029e7a39e6b782ed361aa94b93f70854f002ad686cfd6d6f27eb6f042d9ba8e4ee87a33ff757b60b9f8cf3665f0245>,
   events
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e54f79c92952c161ebb69bbb3772965e4964dc12b3636136adec12064f0d73997ae71857657a569ef75014b82348193a6c04fa42793c2a2d82>
and
   resources
   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5f6e53858d48a9d0763e91a3c9f1ded338248ec45c9deb010ee7997beb72954450646b78860afb38b91e93047a04a196e492ce4695d3448e1>
on
   business planning, marketing and cash flow.

Get in touch with the *Service NSW Business Bureau * to take advantage of
these and many other valuable government programs.

[image: Upgrade and save]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e529f147cd51f7c4cfa7748c15c17c5c2545e5f4255b6c1fe31f99e80dbca616f8b5f50ea5a07a957a7b05c50b95be4554bde58326607f72ef>
[image: Hands holding a mobile phone displaying a map with emergency and
hazard warnings]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e54887a842aba77b8cb07e5084453083e2db26cd6a0c0ea882fd8fb78b40dfe308940d4072e368b3f5f21b4c92bec32d19f175d325545f710a>
Financial incentives to electrify your fleet
It costs *70% less to run* an electric vehicle (EV) and *40% less to
maintain*. Now the *NSW Government* is helping you reduce the upfront costs
too.

If your business has a fleet of at least 3 vehicles, you may be eligible to
claim* $5,000* to put towards the purchase of an EV passenger vehicle, and
up to *$20,000* per EV truck.

You can also claim *$4,000 to $8,000 for the supply and installation of
smart chargers at your premises.  *

[image: Download Hazards Near Me app]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5759c7a4710b97d44e145fbf120c9dfb0fa4b7cbd2aa204ef073f5267f2cb9993180f628a2941b922db51ffae9eb1502310ccb2bb0fb96a8b>
[image: Two men sitting across from each other smiling and shaking hands in
agreement]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5b67bb0ae33120f664c2d656bf14ee58341841a4f373deb97148853c3fccb4fcd85a56222dfdc81fe483a34ad98168931474a2a803aeb3624>
Employee Super Guarantee payments due soon
As an employer, it's important to always pay your workersâ€™ Superannuation
Guarantee (SG) at the correct rate (currently 11.5%), into the right fund
and *before the due date*.

Mistakes could lead to additional paperwork, charges and penalties.

The next due date to make mandatory quarterly SG contributions is *28
January 2025*.

If you're falling behind with your SG obligations, contact the *Australian
Taxation Office* so they can help get you back on track.

[image: Contact the mediation team]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e562e6cde855bbe30d31a12916b896ef107ee85c65a97a062ea0ad9fbbdef52fcfd690a53fa96a1d5bfe0e543ad050a15ae380b45f0807dd64>
[image: Lithium-ion batteries displaying a recycling symbol]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5af9dc4f34f3c8585f586b859a61c543f7fade5f46d202aa27f4d32145f52ae83eb6c5bf059626fa26b6a90114a86b5c468de59c027d5479e>
Recognise potential with more than just praise
Nominate your outstanding trainees or apprentices for the *NSW Training
Awards 2025*.

This is a powerful way to show your *appreciation* and *support *for
their *hard
work* and *dedication*.

You can also nominate high-performing trainers, training organisations and
employers.

[image: See top safety tips]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5d52bb2f1b4a1a67693b4ade5f2ee4ec0d75b381ed33c855787220e39a612eb3ea34c29171034d75cba98c5d077989a1c864f2d0c33924738>

*Cyber security uplift*
Tips for business | January 2025

The best software version is the latest version

A scammer starts by researching your organisation, then sends an email that
appears to be from a colleague or business, asking you to click on a link
to fix an administrative issue. *Don't click â€“ it's a trap! *

*Hover over the sender address and link to be sure the email is legit.*
Contact the Service NSW Business Bureau to get support
Call 13 77 88 <137788> Monday to Friday 8am to 5pm.

For interpreter services, call 13 14 50 <131450> and ask the interpreter to
call 13 77 88 <137788>.

[image: Book a call back]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e50623b3538e5c12b1ce23a332c0729510caa57b9fc5c71499f2b964842aac71f5415471d4d76d0ee6435e8c28f197550b82971d41fc9d704f>
[image: Facebook]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5cc1498c0090fecbc4b6e66cecad5050f7d9e65d0c2ea322ed493db92d54f081d6528b28a6fdd83f851c8ab30658545621d5734f5f336337e>
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e58168aca8fac4ee9971c70af1a7f22b52f8fa3a86ea70b582ddfea23590a3551e75bcd5b8d237e88ea2e4137d5adf6c1bc2f3d1ee6ce4dde4>
[image: Instagram]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5cf472cae4ed20ec0214f1621edb1bc45a22fe46b8d16f1bc184743fa6c4634256c21207053382a18da4ceed20e5d6946cd14981b404c801a>
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5505aeb35dd4ccce5fd190f21ef1d7fac8c6d6074d29c79d5943d1cd587bde94f905d292e9cf073a873b768b8b08cde126ba1bc1c56a2e7f6>

About this email

This email was sent to wnaz0410@gmail.com by the NSW Government, 2
<https://www.google.com/maps/search/2+24+Rawson+Place+Sydney,+NSW,+2000?entry=gmail&source=g>
â€“24 Rawson Place Sydney, NSW, 2000
<https://www.google.com/maps/search/2+24+Rawson+Place+Sydney,+NSW,+2000?entry=gmail&source=g>
.

You are receiving this email because you have listed your business with the
ATO's Australian Business Register (ABR). The NSW Government can access the
ABR database subject to terms and conditions.

Unsubscribe
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e52710865a2020775db89ea7cf8377123185cbd679e6ce8653684b5592e0cbbc61bc41711a93c05d3b4b6ea24a2991b88bd881c41ab7c5ceeb>
if you do not wish to receive any business updates from the NSW Government.

See the *NSW Government Privacy Statement
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5cb4de838ac9ab6ca7e48600c181380d544eb18139a5125c8adeb6a5b489a99483f37da3882cc32b252c33bd2886d1ad05eb9e986813632cf>*
to learn how we use and protect your personal information.

emails.subject: Fwd: Meeting Summary for Catch up with Raghav
emails.content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Meeting Summary with AI Companion <no-reply@zoom.us>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2025 at 10:05
Subject: Meeting Summary for Catch up with Raghav
To: <john@riverdalecloud.com>


<https://zoom.com>
Meeting summary with AI Companion now supports additional languages in
preview. Learn More
<https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0058013#languages>
*Meeting summary for Catch up with Raghav (01/22/2025)*
*Quick recap*
John and Raghav discussed their personal experiences, business journeys,
and the potential for collaboration in the technology and business sectors.
They also explored the company's focus on sales and marketing, the
confidence in their product, and the office environment's impact on
software engineers. Lastly, they discussed potential business
opportunities, including expanding into the US market and creating a
product or service to help people with lifestyle issues.
*Next steps*
â€¢ John to connect Raghav with Sandeep for further discussions about the
business and product.
â€¢ Raghav to visit Riverdale's office again to spend time with Sandeep and
potentially talk to some engineers.
â€¢ John to consider Raghav's offer to help expand into the US market and
potentially set up meetings with connections.
â€¢ Raghav to provide feedback to John after speaking with Sandeep and the
team.
â€¢ John to think over plans for the US market and potentially ask Raghav for
specific help.
â€¢ Raghav to continue developing his Action Health Hub idea and consider
potential collaborations with John.
*Summary*
*Personal Experiences and Business Challenges*
John and Raghav discussed their personal experiences and interests,
including their weekend activities and their love for cricket. Raghav
shared his experience of playing cricket in the US and his connection to
Alvin Kalicharan, a West Indies player. They also discussed the potential
of their office, which Raghav suggested could be better utilized. John
shared his experience of being the sole investor in his business and the
challenges he faced during the Covid-19 pandemic. Raghav encouraged John to
take educated risks and adapt to the current AI revolution, emphasizing the
importance of being an early adopter in any revolution.
*Exploring AI Agents and Expertise*
John and Raghav discussed their respective experiences and expertise in the
technology and business sectors. Raghav shared his background in product
development, leadership, and coaching, while John shared his journey as a
lone entrepreneur in the business, focusing on cloud computing. They also
discussed the potential of AI agents in CRM and their impact on the market.
Raghav expressed his interest in leveraging AI agents to enhance healthcare
in India, a future idea he is considering. The conversation ended with a
mutual understanding of their respective areas of expertise and potential
collaboration opportunities.
*Business Evolution and Managed Services*
Raghav and John discussed their respective journeys and the evolution of
their businesses. Raghav shared his background, which included a transition
from a traditional job to a more tech-focused role. John, on the other
hand, shared his journey with Riverdale, which started with implementation
and has since expanded to include product development and managed services.
John highlighted that their focus is now on managed services and product
development, with the managed services generating the major revenue. They
also discussed their plans to launch connectors for other accounting
software like Netsuite and QuickBooks.
*Company Focus on Sales and Marketing*
John discussed the company's focus on sales and marketing, particularly in
the US, UK, and Australia. He mentioned a roadshow across the US and UK,
and the company's growing market in the UK. John also highlighted the
company's presence in India, with a large enterprise having about 300
licenses and 8,000 field service agents. He mentioned that the company gets
inquiries from across the world, with a focus on where their product,
QuickBooks, is growing. Raghav inquired about the company's focus on
specific markets, to which John responded that they focus on where their
product is growing, such as QuickBooks in the US.
*Product Confidence and US Market*
John discussed the confidence in their product due to its platform nature,
which allows for customization and automation of finance functions. He
shared a use case of a manufacturing company that has fully automated its
purchases and sales using their product. John also mentioned that they have
received inquiries about integrating with QuickBooks and NetSuite, but have
not focused much on the US market. He revealed that they had one person
working on sales and marketing in the US, but the results were not clear.
Raghav asked about the market opportunity in the US, to which John
responded that they are confident in their product's ability to win demos.
John also mentioned that they have a lead generator in Pune who identifies
and qualifies leads.
*Office Environment and Talent Retention*
Raghav and John discussed the office environment and its impact on software
engineers. Raghav pointed out that the current office setup was not
conducive for innovation and problem-solving, suggesting a need for a
different environment to foster creativity. John agreed, but noted that
improving the office environment was not a top priority. They also
discussed the company's compensation package, which is a mix of standard
benefits and incentives, aiming to match industry standards to retain
talent. John mentioned that they typically retain resources for about 3 to
4 years, sometimes up to 5 years. The company currently has about 12
engineers in India and sales and marketing staff in Australia.
*Product Management and Revenue Discussion*
John and Raghav discussed their company's product management and revenue.
John confirmed that their product is managed by him and Sandeep, with a
focus on customer expectations and customization. They aim to release at
least four product updates a year. John also mentioned that their business
is profitable and they are not investing anymore. Raghav suggested the
potential for further growth, but John emphasized his focus on their
current product and ensuring profitability. They agreed to discuss revenue
details in a future call.
*Expanding Customer Base and US Market*
John expressed his vision to expand his customer base significantly,
potentially five times the previous year's acquisition, and his desire to
grow exponentially. He acknowledged the need for funding to achieve this
goal. Raghav suggested that he could help John expand into the US market,
leveraging his understanding of the market and connections there. Raghav
proposed setting up calls to discuss John's product and management services
offering in more detail, and to assess the readiness of John's workforce in
India to handle the expected challenges. John agreed to continue the
discussion on this topic.
*SFX and Salesforce Integration Discussed*
Raghav and John discussed their respective clients and products. John,
representing a company that works with the Forest Stewardship Council,
explained their product, Sfx, which is a Salesforce native app that
connects Salesforce and 0, a cloud-based accounting software. Raghav
clarified that Sfx is a Riverdale product. John also mentioned that they
are focusing on the life sciences sector in Australia, with clients like
Nutritia Danone. The conversation ended with Raghav acknowledging these
details.
*Australian Honeymoon and Wildlife Encounters*
John and Raghav reminisced about their travels, particularly their
honeymoon trip to Australia. They discussed their experiences with
wildlife, including a close encounter with a rattlesnake in Western
Australia. John shared his fondness for driving and exploring Australian
shores, while Raghav mentioned their fond memories of beaches in Brisbane.
They also discussed their visit to the Blue Mountains and Philip Island,
where they saw penguins. The conversation ended with John sharing his
recent trip to the Whitsundays and Whitehaven beach.
*Exploring US Market and Business Opportunities*
Raghav and John discussed potential collaborations and business
opportunities. Raghav expressed his interest in tapping into the US market
and asked John for help in setting up connections. John agreed to assist
and mentioned his experience working with other organizations, including a
cyber security product. Raghav shared his idea of creating a product or
service to help people with lifestyle issues, emphasizing the importance of
purpose and quality of life. John agreed to connect Raghav with Sandeep,
who has been in the business for 17 years, and suggested Raghav talk to
engineers to understand the product's development process. They agreed to
connect again for further discussions.

Our records indicate that we are yet to receive the actual wages
declaration for your NSW Workers Compensation insurance for the policy
period(s) listed below. *THESE ARE NOW OVERDUE.*

Employers are legally required to report their actual wages to icare at the
end of each policy period. This helps ensure that your workers compensation
premiums are calculated both accurately and fairly, including any premium
refunds.

If an employer fails to submit their actual wage records, we may undertake
a wage audit, and/or SIRA, the State Insurance Regulatory Authority, may
take the following regulatory action:

   - Issue a penalty notice under Clause 141 of the Workers Compensation
   Regulation 2016
   - Issue an Official Caution
   - Issue late payment fees
   - Referral for a wage audit to be conducted for up to the last 5 years
   - Recover costs associated with a Wage Audit
   - Prosecution - the maximum penalty for this offence is 20 penalty units
   ($2,200).

We do not appear to have received your actual wages declaration for the
following policy periods:

30/06/2020 - 30/06/2021
30/06/2023 - 30/06/2024


*TAKE ACTION NOW:*
Following the directions below, please submit your missing wage
declarations within *45 days of the date of this emai*l.

*Step 2.* To use our self-service functionality, youâ€™ll need:

*Customer Reference Number: *PF7Z34LZ

is correct. If you have more than one policy period overdue, please enter
the oldest first

Declare your Actual wages
<https://comms.icare.nsw.gov.au/link/id/zzzz679064caa02df855Pzzzz666fe2bccf270740/page.html>

*Knowingly declaring incorrect wages or submitting incorrect information
(including your business description), may also result in regulatory action
and/or fines.*




*Expecting a refund*

*Refunds can only be sent if we have your Electronic Funds Transfer (EFT)
bank details linked to your policy. *Call us now on *(02) 8378 0525* to
speak with our dedicated team who can update your policy information with
your bank details so we can process any future refunds quickly and securely.

For further information on how to declare your wages or general information

emails.subject: Fwd: [SPAM] CSD25644 - Assurance and Test Services Arrangement
emails.content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: CSD25644 <CSD25644@customerservice.nsw.gov.au>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2025 at 05:25
Subject: [SPAM] CSD25644 - Assurance and Test Services Arrangement
To:


Dear *NSW based local supplier*,



The Department of Customer Service (DCS) will soon be releasing a Request
for Tender (RFT) for Assurance and Test Services Arrangement.  As of 9th
September 2024, the Procurement Board has issued a new Procurement Board
Direction 2024-02, which requires agencies to identify capable local
suppliers during the planning phase for all procurements valued at $7.5
million or more. This ensures that local suppliers have a full and fair
opportunity to participate in these procurement processes.



*About this Tender*



This RFT seeks to establish a panel of pre-qualified Suppliers to deliver
General and Specialised Testing Services for DCS programmes. Testing
services will be across two categories:



â€¢            Category A - Provision of General Testing Services

â€¢            Category B - Provision of Specialised Security/Penetration
Testing



Services include Test Management, Functional, Non-Functional, Automated
Regression, and Penetration Testing, leveraging modern practices such as
agile and Gen AI. Engagements will be governed under ICTA agreements,
initiated via a streamlined order form.



Respondents applying for Category A and/or Category B will be assessed
separately for each category using the same evaluation criteria (check for
and/or to determine specific requirement) to determine their eligibility.
Respondents may apply, at their discretion, for either Category A, Category
B, or both. In cases where a respondent applies for both categories, they
may be selected for one, neither, or both categories. The potential
outcomes of the evaluation process are as follows:



1.          Successful for Category A and unsuccessful for Category B.

2.          Unsuccessful for Category A and successful for Category B.

3.          Unsuccessful for both Category A and Category B.

4.          Successful for both Category A and Category B.



*Tender Publication Date*



DCS is targeting January 2025 to publish the RFT.



*What you need to do*



You can register your interest by responding to this email including full
business name and ABN/ACN and key contact details.  We will then ensure you
receive an email when the RFT is published via buy.nsw tenders or inform
you if there are unforeseen delays.  You should also ensure you are
registered as an Advanced Supplier on buy.nsw  (Link https://buy.nsw.gov.au/).




*Please note -*  We are unable to provide further information about this
tender at this time, to ensure that all suppliers receive the full details
of the tender at the same time . Further, DCS reserves the right in its
absolute discretion to suspend or terminate the tender process or approach
at any time of our choosing.



Kind regards,



CSD25644 Procurement Team

Email: CSD25644@customerservice.nsw.gov.au

From: The Zoho Deluge Team <mike.a@zohocreator.com>

Subject: Get to know Deluge: Zohoâ€™s powerful scripting language
To: <john@riverdalecloud.com.au>





[image:
https://stratus.campaign-image.com/images/786401028953746995_zc_v1_1716546616551_creator_logo_lockup.jpg]

Hi there,

As a Zoho One user, you're already familiar with our suite and its
customization capabilities across our products. Central to this is Deluge,
our online low-code scripting language that powers the Zoho suite!

Designed with advanced featuresâ€”such as drag-and-drop code blocks,
serverless development, and a user-friendly syntaxâ€”Deluge enables you to
automate business processes and enhance your Zoho products with
capabilities beyond their default offerings.

Weâ€™re excited to offer a *free,* three-day introductory training
initiative, part of the *Get to Know* series, to introduce you to Zoho
Deluge and its application in CRM, Desk, Books, and Creator. This program
is the perfect way to familiarize yourself with the role and impact of
Deluge at Zoho.

Day 1: Introduction to Deluge as a scripting language
Day 2: Deluge applications across Zoho products (Zoho CRM, Zoho Desk)

Workplace trends

Hiring

Hired or haunted?

One in five jobs advertised online is a â€˜ghost positionâ€™, meaning that
companies have no intention of actually hiring for the role, according to a
2024 data report by hiring platform Greenhouse. According to hiring
experts, these phantom postings have increased for various reasons
including companies wanting to create an illusion of growth, employers
having to comply with laws requiring public job postings despite having
internal candidates, or staffing agencies creating fictional positions to
enhance their portfolios when pitching to clients. This practice
contributes to a perplexing reality for US workers: economic indicators
suggest a robust hiring environment, with 256,000 new jobs added in
December, yet white-collar professionals increasingly report difficulty
securing positions. This disconnect between advertised opportunities and
actual hiring intentions is creating a troubling layer of opacity in the
modern job market.



Trade

As restrictions lift, Syrian shelves are stocked to the brim

Syria is experiencing a significant transformation in its consumer market
following former dictator Bashar al-Assad's ousting. The new government has
lifted previous restrictions on foreign currency and has reduced import
tariffs, which under Assad had been so extreme that iPhones faced duties of
nearly $900. As a result, thereâ€™s been an influx of international products
that had been largely absent during the 13-year civil war. Now, Damascus
stores are stocked with imported goods from Turkey, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon,
and Western brands, marking a dramatic shift from the Assad era when
foreign products were hidden and sold secretly due to security risks. This
change represents a significant departure from Assad's policies, and
economists expect it to welcome a new and, hopefully, more prosperous era
for the Syrian people.

The AI corner

Legislation

The UK government is betting big on AI in 2025

UK Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer unveiled a comprehensive vision for
leveraging AI to revitalize public services and drive economic growth in a
landmark speech last week. His plan, coined "AI Opportunities Action Plan,"
outlines the government's strategy to harness AI's potential and is backed
by leading UK tech firms pledging Â£14 billion ($17.35 billion) for various
initiatives, projected to create more than 13,000 jobs. Specific key
proposals include establishing "AI Growth Zones" across the country to
accelerate infrastructure development and employment opportunities as well
as implementing AI-powered camera systems for efficient road maintenance
and pothole detection. This ambitious plan aims to position the UK as a
global AI leader in Europe and the world.



Development

France is rising up as Europe's new AI powerhouse

France is emerging as a prime destination for launching AI companies,
driven by a surge in entrepreneurship over the past two decades, increased
availability of venture capital, and President Emmanuel Macron's active
support for the sector. The country is now challenging London, which is
also vying for the position of Europe's AI hub. However, one of France's
key differentiators is its startups focusing on open-source models that
foster collaboration and wider access to technology. This approach aims to
provide a competitive advantage in applying AI across various economic
sectors. And while potential regulatory burdens imposed by the EU's AI Act
and the temptation for top Paris-based AI startups to relocate to the US to
be closer to their consumer base are causing concern, the countryâ€™s
commitment to innovation is still positioning it as a formidable player in
the global AI landscape.

Getting your team on board

In this week's episode, Adam Goldstein shares his tips for rallying your
team around an inspiring vision.

Listen to the full episode
<https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/UPj3n7EBlBOmDl6uKSs0OA~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRpcjbdP0RcaHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuLnNwb3RpZnkuY29tL2VwaXNvZGUvNlVZOExDcUdRS3JMdktva3Jpa2U0Zj9zaT0xZDQwZWE1NjMzZDU0NjIyJmxpZD1sYjZ5MWRiNTQ4c2lXA3NwY0IKZ47dsY9n_Cld8FIXam9obkByaXZlcmRhbGVjbG91ZC5jb21YBAAAALs~>

Being strategic about employee promotions

By monday.com
<https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/MuifdnymFeB0OH4H1svUaA~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRpcjbdP0R0aHR0cHM6Ly9tb25kYXkuY29tLz91dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9YnJhemUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW11bHRpLWVuLW90aGVyLW11bHRpLW4lMkZhLWVtYWlsJmxpZD1rZGQ3dXNoYTQybW9XA3NwY0IKZ47dsY9n_Cld8FIXam9obkByaXZlcmRhbGVjbG91ZC5jb21YBAAAALs~>

With the new year underway, many employees are reflecting on their career
growth. And as you consider promotions, itâ€™s important to think about both
your team membersâ€™ personal aspirations and how you want to evolve your org
chart for maximum future success. Your job as a manager is, after all, to
develop your team to continuously accomplish bigger goals, and the right
timing and approach to promotions can accelerate your collective impact.



71% of employees believe that hiring from within is better for scaling a
business than hiring externally, according to a study by Joblist. With your
current team members having a much deeper knowledge of your business than
new hires, promoting tenured employees into senior roles means less
catch-up in company-related areas, since they are building on their
existing experience.



That said, promotions must be handled carefully because they affect team
morale and employee retention. In fact, 50% of workers said they would look
for a new job if they donâ€™t receive their expected promotion, per iCIMSâ€™
2024 Workforce Report.



So, how do you make the right promotion decisions that will position your
team for long-term success?



Identify your big-picture goal

Now is a good time to evaluate, or re-evaluate, where you want your
department to be this year, and even over the next few years. Consider
documenting what you want to accomplish at these stages and which resources
you will need to put into place to realize those goals. Be very specific
about the types of outcomes you want and what your ideal org chart might
look like. As you do this, think about which of your team members have the
right skills or potential to fill those roles. Remember to make this an
exploratory stage and donâ€™t come to any conclusions before you do some
deeper digging.



Understand desired growth paths

When planning how you want your team to evolve, itâ€™s very important that
you check in with each of your employees. Donâ€™t assume you know how a
particular team member sees their career trajectory; ask them directly and
try to remove any bias or pressure to move in one way or the other. Do your
best to find out what drives them and what kind of work really excites
them. And remember that not all of your employees will want to or be fit to
evolve into managerial roles. So, make it clear that growth can come in all
forms and that meaningful career paths can involve deepening skillsets or
taking on larger projects over time.



Set clear and measurable benchmarks

When you have career advancement discussions, be sure to set clear goals
for each employee to achieve before they move to the next seniority level â€“
and discuss how each of those goals will be measured and quantified. 86% of
HR leaders believe that their organizationsâ€™ career paths are unclear for
employees, according to Gartner, highlighting the existing gap when it
comes to this kind of clarity. For this reason, you need to be very
consistent about benchmarks to alleviate disparate expectations and
feelings of bias or resentment among team members. Find a way to
continuously track these goals, whether itâ€™s through work management
software or in specific employee documents reviewed in your one-on-ones.



Seek several sources

Success metrics are definitely crucial for promotion intel, but there are
also soft skills, interpersonal relationships, and other factors that
should inform your decision-making. Be proactive about discovering who is
contributing the most to projects. If youâ€™re seeing mentions of the same
person in several messaging threads or noticing someone always stepping in
to help, be sure to clock that information. Also, keep an eye out for
employees who are going above and beyond and showing a work ethic that can
be channeled and developed into leadership. Getting this kind of
information from all sides will help best inform your approach to team
growth and make absolutely sure youâ€™re promoting the right people at the
right time.



Recognize team impact

The challenging truth is that not everyone on the team will be promoted,
even when they might expect to be. Thatâ€™s why having clear benchmarks and
consistent expectations is key to minimizing the negative feelings that may
arise among those who are not advanced during a particular cycle. Make sure
you have a strong communication plan in place and that before you announce
the promotions on your team, you reiterate your focus on key benchmarks
that dictate advancement. Remind your team that some of their goals at
their current level might still be in progress, which is why itâ€™s natural
for advancement to happen at different stages for different people.



On a similar note, when handled the right way, seeing teammates get
promoted can actually spark motivation and build a sense of trust in the
process. It demonstrates that the system is fair and based on clear,
achievable criteria, encouraging everyone to stay focused on their personal
growth.

Water cooler chatter

JPMorgan disabled employee discussions amid return-to-office backlash. The
bank's internal memo last week mandated all 300,000 employees to work
full-time from the office starting in March. After sharing the news on
their internal company website, JPMorgan was inundated with comments from
concerned employees addressing commuting costs, childcare issues, and
work-life balance concerns. As a result, the bank reportedly swiftly shut
down the comment functionality to silence further group discussion.

â€œWe know that some of you prefer a hybrid schedule and respectfully
understand that not everyone will agree with this decision.â€

- JP Morgan, Memo

2024 was the hottest year weâ€™ve ever had. The European Copernicus climate
service, a main global data provider, recently reported that last year was
the first to pass the 1.5C global warming limit, despite world leaders
vowing a decade ago they would work to avoid this.

â€œI think it's safe to say that both 2023 and 2024 temperatures surprised
most climate scientists - we didn't think we'd be seeing a year above 1.5C
this early.â€

- Zeke Hausfather, Climatologist

Question of the week

Last weekâ€™s answer: Finland, where the average worker drinks about 12 kg
(26 lbs) of coffee per year- equivalent to around 4 cups a day!

This weekâ€™s question: What percentage of professionals report chronic
exhaustion?

Just for laughs

â€œHave I said enough nice things to move on to the negative feedback yet?â€

Meeting summary for Catch up with Raghav (01/22/2025)
Quick recap
John and Raghav discussed their personal experiences, business journeys, and the potential for collaboration in the technology and business sectors. They also explored the company's focus on sales and marketing, the confidence in their product, and the office environment's impact on software engineers. Lastly, they discussed potential business opportunities, including expanding into the US market and creating a product or service to help people with lifestyle issues.
Next steps
â€¢ John to connect Raghav with Sandeep for further discussions about the business and product.
â€¢ Raghav to visit Riverdale's office again to spend time with Sandeep and potentially talk to some engineers.
â€¢ John to consider Raghav's offer to help expand into the US market and potentially set up meetings with connections.
â€¢ Raghav to provide feedback to John after speaking with Sandeep and the team.
â€¢ John to think over plans for the US market and potentially ask Raghav for specific help.
â€¢ Raghav to continue developing his Action Health Hub idea and consider potential collaborations with John.
Summary
Personal Experiences and Business Challenges
John and Raghav discussed their personal experiences and interests, including their weekend activities and their love for cricket. Raghav shared his experience of playing cricket in the US and his connection to Alvin Kalicharan, a West Indies player. They also discussed the potential of their office, which Raghav suggested could be better utilized. John shared his experience of being the sole investor in his business and the challenges he faced during the Covid-19 pandemic. Raghav encouraged John to take educated risks and adapt to the current AI revolution, emphasizing the importance of being an early adopter in any revolution.
Exploring AI Agents and Expertise
John and Raghav discussed their respective experiences and expertise in the technology and business sectors. Raghav shared his background in product development, leadership, and coaching, while John shared his journey as a lone entrepreneur in the business, focusing on cloud computing. They also discussed the potential of AI agents in CRM and their impact on the market. Raghav expressed his interest in leveraging AI agents to enhance healthcare in India, a future idea he is considering. The conversation ended with a mutual understanding of their respective areas of expertise and potential collaboration opportunities.
Business Evolution and Managed Services
Raghav and John discussed their respective journeys and the evolution of their businesses. Raghav shared his background, which included a transition from a traditional job to a more tech-focused role. John, on the other hand, shared his journey with Riverdale, which started with implementation and has since expanded to include product development and managed services. John highlighted that their focus is now on managed services and product development, with the managed services generating the major revenue. They also discussed their plans to launch connectors for other accounting software like Netsuite and QuickBooks.
Company Focus on Sales and Marketing
John discussed the company's focus on sales and marketing, particularly in the US, UK, and Australia. He mentioned a roadshow across the US and UK, and the company's growing market in the UK. John also highlighted the company's presence in India, with a large enterprise having about 300 licenses and 8,000 field service agents. He mentioned that the company gets inquiries from across the world, with a focus on where their product, QuickBooks, is growing. Raghav inquired about the company's focus on specific markets, to which John responded that they focus on where their product is growing, such as QuickBooks in the US.
Product Confidence and US Market
John discussed the confidence in their product due to its platform nature, which allows for customization and automation of finance functions. He shared a use case of a manufacturing company that has fully automated its purchases and sales using their product. John also mentioned that they have received inquiries about integrating with QuickBooks and NetSuite, but have not focused much on the US market. He revealed that they had one person working on sales and marketing in the US, but the results were not clear. Raghav asked about the market opportunity in the US, to which John responded that they are confident in their product's ability to win demos. John also mentioned that they have a lead generator in Pune who identifies and qualifies leads.
Office Environment and Talent Retention
Raghav and John discussed the office environment and its impact on software engineers. Raghav pointed out that the current office setup was not conducive for innovation and problem-solving, suggesting a need for a different environment to foster creativity. John agreed, but noted that improving the office environment was not a top priority. They also discussed the company's compensation package, which is a mix of standard benefits and incentives, aiming to match industry standards to retain talent. John mentioned that they typically retain resources for about 3 to 4 years, sometimes up to 5 years. The company currently has about 12 engineers in India and sales and marketing staff in Australia.
Product Management and Revenue Discussion
John and Raghav discussed their company's product management and revenue. John confirmed that their product is managed by him and Sandeep, with a focus on customer expectations and customization. They aim to release at least four product updates a year. John also mentioned that their business is profitable and they are not investing anymore. Raghav suggested the potential for further growth, but John emphasized his focus on their current product and ensuring profitability. They agreed to discuss revenue details in a future call.
Expanding Customer Base and US Market
John expressed his vision to expand his customer base significantly, potentially five times the previous year's acquisition, and his desire to grow exponentially. He acknowledged the need for funding to achieve this goal. Raghav suggested that he could help John expand into the US market, leveraging his understanding of the market and connections there. Raghav proposed setting up calls to discuss John's product and management services offering in more detail, and to assess the readiness of John's workforce in India to handle the expected challenges. John agreed to continue the discussion on this topic.
SFX and Salesforce Integration Discussed
Raghav and John discussed their respective clients and products. John, representing a company that works with the Forest Stewardship Council, explained their product, Sfx, which is a Salesforce native app that connects Salesforce and 0, a cloud-based accounting software. Raghav clarified that Sfx is a Riverdale product. John also mentioned that they are focusing on the life sciences sector in Australia, with clients like Nutritia Danone. The conversation ended with Raghav acknowledging these details.
Australian Honeymoon and Wildlife Encounters
John and Raghav reminisced about their travels, particularly their honeymoon trip to Australia. They discussed their experiences with wildlife, including a close encounter with a rattlesnake in Western Australia. John shared his fondness for driving and exploring Australian shores, while Raghav mentioned their fond memories of beaches in Brisbane. They also discussed their visit to the Blue Mountains and Philip Island, where they saw penguins. The conversation ended with John sharing his recent trip to the Whitsundays and Whitehaven beach.
Exploring US Market and Business Opportunities
Raghav and John discussed potential collaborations and business opportunities. Raghav expressed his interest in tapping into the US market and asked John for help in setting up connections. John agreed to assist and mentioned his experience working with other organizations, including a cyber security product. Raghav shared his idea of creating a product or service to help people with lifestyle issues, emphasizing the importance of purpose and quality of life. John agreed to connect Raghav with Sandeep, who has been in the business for 17 years, and suggested Raghav talk to engineers to understand the product's development process. They agreed to connect again for further discussions.

   <https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5f6e53858d48a9d0763e91a3c9f1ded338248ec45c9deb010ee7997beb72954450646b78860afb38b91e93047a04a196e492ce4695d3448e1>
on
   business planning, marketing and cash flow.

Get in touch with the *Service NSW Business Bureau * to take advantage of
these and many other valuable government programs.

[image: Upgrade and save]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e529f147cd51f7c4cfa7748c15c17c5c2545e5f4255b6c1fe31f99e80dbca616f8b5f50ea5a07a957a7b05c50b95be4554bde58326607f72ef>
[image: Hands holding a mobile phone displaying a map with emergency and
hazard warnings]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e54887a842aba77b8cb07e5084453083e2db26cd6a0c0ea882fd8fb78b40dfe308940d4072e368b3f5f21b4c92bec32d19f175d325545f710a>
Financial incentives to electrify your fleet
It costs *70% less to run* an electric vehicle (EV) and *40% less to
maintain*. Now the *NSW Government* is helping you reduce the upfront costs
too.

If your business has a fleet of at least 3 vehicles, you may be eligible to
claim* $5,000* to put towards the purchase of an EV passenger vehicle, and
up to *$20,000* per EV truck.

You can also claim *$4,000 to $8,000 for the supply and installation of
smart chargers at your premises.  *

[image: Download Hazards Near Me app]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5759c7a4710b97d44e145fbf120c9dfb0fa4b7cbd2aa204ef073f5267f2cb9993180f628a2941b922db51ffae9eb1502310ccb2bb0fb96a8b>
[image: Two men sitting across from each other smiling and shaking hands in
agreement]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5b67bb0ae33120f664c2d656bf14ee58341841a4f373deb97148853c3fccb4fcd85a56222dfdc81fe483a34ad98168931474a2a803aeb3624>
Employee Super Guarantee payments due soon
As an employer, it's important to always pay your workersâ€™ Superannuation
Guarantee (SG) at the correct rate (currently 11.5%), into the right fund
and *before the due date*.

Mistakes could lead to additional paperwork, charges and penalties.

The next due date to make mandatory quarterly SG contributions is *28
January 2025*.

If you're falling behind with your SG obligations, contact the *Australian
Taxation Office* so they can help get you back on track.

[image: Contact the mediation team]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e562e6cde855bbe30d31a12916b896ef107ee85c65a97a062ea0ad9fbbdef52fcfd690a53fa96a1d5bfe0e543ad050a15ae380b45f0807dd64>
[image: Lithium-ion batteries displaying a recycling symbol]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5af9dc4f34f3c8585f586b859a61c543f7fade5f46d202aa27f4d32145f52ae83eb6c5bf059626fa26b6a90114a86b5c468de59c027d5479e>
Recognise potential with more than just praise
Nominate your outstanding trainees or apprentices for the *NSW Training
Awards 2025*.

This is a powerful way to show your *appreciation* and *support *for
their *hard
work* and *dedication*.

You can also nominate high-performing trainers, training organisations and
employers.

[image: See top safety tips]
<https://click.comms.service.nsw.gov.au/?qs=ba7376211a1213e5d52bb2f1b4a1a67693b4ade5f2ee4ec0d75b381ed33c855787220e39a612eb3ea34c29171034d75cba98c5d077989a1c864f2d0c33924738>

*Cyber security uplift*
Tips for business | January 2025

The best software version is the latest version

A scammer starts by researching your organisation, then sends an email that
appears to be from a colleague or business, asking you to click on a link
to fix an administrative issue. *Don't click â€“ it's a trap! *

*Hover over the sender address and link to be sure the email is legit.*
Contact the Service NSW Business Bureau to get support
Call 13 77 88 <137788> Monday to Friday 8am to 5pm.

For interpreter services, call 13 14 50 <131450> and ask the interpreter to
call 13 77 88 <137788>.

emails.subject: [SPAM] CSD25644 - Assurance and Test Services Arrangement
emails.content:
Dear NSW based local supplier,

The Department of Customer Service (DCS) will soon be releasing a Request for Tender (RFT) for Assurance and Test Services Arrangement.  As of 9th September 2024, the Procurement Board has issued a new Procurement Board Direction 2024-02, which requires agencies to identify capable local suppliers during the planning phase for all procurements valued at $7.5 million or more. This ensures that local suppliers have a full and fair opportunity to participate in these procurement processes.

About this Tender

This RFT seeks to establish a panel of pre-qualified Suppliers to deliver General and Specialised Testing Services for DCS programmes. Testing services will be across two categories:

*            Category A - Provision of General Testing Services
*            Category B - Provision of Specialised Security/Penetration Testing

Services include Test Management, Functional, Non-Functional, Automated Regression, and Penetration Testing, leveraging modern practices such as agile and Gen AI. Engagements will be governed under ICTA agreements, initiated via a streamlined order form.

Respondents applying for Category A and/or Category B will be assessed separately for each category using the same evaluation criteria (check for and/or to determine specific requirement) to determine their eligibility. Respondents may apply, at their discretion, for either Category A, Category B, or both. In cases where a respondent applies for both categories, they may be selected for one, neither, or both categories. The potential outcomes of the evaluation process are as follows:

1.          Successful for Category A and unsuccessful for Category B.
2.          Unsuccessful for Category A and successful for Category B.
3.          Unsuccessful for both Category A and Category B.
4.          Successful for both Category A and Category B.

Tender Publication Date

DCS is targeting January 2025 to publish the RFT.

What you need to do

You can register your interest by responding to this email including full business name and ABN/ACN and key contact details.  We will then ensure you receive an email when the RFT is published via buy.nsw tenders or inform you if there are unforeseen delays.  You should also ensure you are registered as an Advanced Supplier on buy.nsw  (Link https://buy.nsw.gov.au/).

Please note -  We are unable to provide further information about this tender at this time, to ensure that all suppliers receive the full details of the tender at the same time . Further, DCS reserves the right in its absolute discretion to suspend or terminate the tender process or approach at any time of our choosing.

Kind regards,

CSD25644 Procurement Team
Email: CSD25644@customerservice.nsw.gov.au<mailto:CSD25644@customerservice.nsw.gov.au>

emails.subject: [samiuat] Change in Salesforce Schema on your Heroku Connect add-on [samiuat]
emails.content:
Heroku Connect has encountered the following issue:


* **Connection**: [samiuat](https://connect.heroku.com/action/overview/2-virginia/e35850fd-ea25-4154-903a-7a4ab48d1a67)
* **Time**: 2025-01-21 at 22:35:16 UTC
* **Details**: The schema for the Product2 mapping has changed in Salesforce. Field has been removed from Salesforce: base\_premium\_\_c. Edit the mapping to remove it from Heroku Connect. 


For more information and any action you need to take, please review the following:


* **Read**: [Dev Center: Check: Salesforce Field Changes](https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/heroku-connect-diagnose#check-salesforce-field-changes)




Thank you,  
The Heroku Connect Team

emails.content:
Heroku Connect has encountered the following issue:


* **Connection**: [samiuat](https://connect.heroku.com/action/overview/2-virginia/e35850fd-ea25-4154-903a-7a4ab48d1a67)
* **Time**: 2025-01-21 at 22:35:15 UTC
* **Details**: The schema for the Endorsement\_\_c mapping has changed in Salesforce. Length has increased in Salesforce for fields: definitions\_\_c, label\_\_c. When you save the mapping, Heroku Connect will alter your database tables to match the Salesforce definition. 


For more information and any action you need to take, please review the following:

Thank you,  
The Heroku Connect Team

Workplace trends

Hiring

Hired or haunted?

One in five jobs advertised online is a â€˜ghost positionâ€™,
meaning that companies have no intention of actually hiring for
the role, according to a 2024 data report by hiring platform
Greenhouse. According to hiring experts, these phantom postings
have increased for various reasons including companies wanting to
create an illusion of growth, employers having to comply with
laws requiring public job postings despite having internal
candidates, or staffing agencies creating fictional positions to
enhance their portfolios when pitching to clients. This practice
contributes to a perplexing reality for US workers: economic
indicators suggest a robust hiring environment, with 256,000 new
jobs added in December, yet white-collar professionals
increasingly report difficulty securing positions. This
disconnect between advertised opportunities and actual hiring
intentions is creating a troubling layer of opacity in the modern
job market.

Trade

As restrictions lift, Syrian shelves are stocked to the brim

Syria is experiencing a significant transformation in its
consumer market following former dictator Bashar al-Assad's
ousting. The new government has lifted previous restrictions on
foreign currency and has reduced import tariffs, which under
Assad had been so extreme that iPhones faced duties of nearly
$900. As a result, thereâ€™s been an influx of international
products that had been largely absent during the 13-year civil
war. Now, Damascus stores are stocked with imported goods from
Turkey, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon, and Western brands, marking a
dramatic shift from the Assad era when foreign products were
hidden and sold secretly due to security risks. This change
represents a significant departure from Assad's policies, and
economists expect it to welcome a new and, hopefully, more
prosperous era for the Syrian people.

The AI corner

Legislation

The UK government is betting big on AI in 2025

UK Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer unveiled a comprehensive
vision for leveraging AI to revitalize public services and drive
economic growth in a landmark speech last week. His plan, coined
"AI Opportunities Action Plan," outlines the government's
strategy to harness AI's potential and is backed by leading UK
tech firms pledging Â£14 billion ($17.35 billion) for various
initiatives, projected to create more than 13,000 jobs. Specific
key proposals include establishing "AI Growth Zones" across the
country to accelerate infrastructure development and employment
opportunities as well as implementing AI-powered camera systems
for efficient road maintenance and pothole detection. This
ambitious plan aims to position the UK as a global AI leader in
Europe and the world.

Development

France is rising up as Europe's new AI powerhouse

France is emerging as a prime destination for launching AI
companies, driven by a surge in entrepreneurship over the past
two decades, increased availability of venture capital, and
President Emmanuel Macron's active support for the sector. The
country is now challenging London, which is also vying for the
position of Europe's AI hub. However, one of France's key
differentiators is its startups focusing on open-source models
that foster collaboration and wider access to technology. This
approach aims to provide a competitive advantage in applying AI
across various economic sectors. And while potential regulatory
burdens imposed by the EU's AI Act and the temptation for top
Paris-based AI startups to relocate to the US to be closer to
their consumer base are causing concern, the countryâ€™s commitment
to innovation is still positioning it as a formidable player in
the global AI landscape.

Getting your team on
board

In this week's episode, Adam Goldstein shares his tips for
rallying your team around an inspiring vision.

Listen to the full episode 
( https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/UPj3n7EBlBOmDl6uKSs0OA~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRpcjbdP0RcaHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuLnNwb3RpZnkuY29tL2VwaXNvZGUvNlVZOExDcUdRS3JMdktva3Jpa2U0Zj9zaT0xZDQwZWE1NjMzZDU0NjIyJmxpZD1sYjZ5MWRiNTQ4c2lXA3NwY0IKZ47dsY9n_Cld8FIXam9obkByaXZlcmRhbGVjbG91ZC5jb21YBAAAALs~ )


Being strategic about employee promotions

By monday.com 
( https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/MuifdnymFeB0OH4H1svUaA~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRpcjbdP0R0aHR0cHM6Ly9tb25kYXkuY29tLz91dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9YnJhemUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW11bHRpLWVuLW90aGVyLW11bHRpLW4lMkZhLWVtYWlsJmxpZD1rZGQ3dXNoYTQybW9XA3NwY0IKZ47dsY9n_Cld8FIXam9obkByaXZlcmRhbGVjbG91ZC5jb21YBAAAALs~ )


With the new year underway, many employees are
reflecting on their career growth. And as you consider
promotions, itâ€™s important to think about both your team membersâ€™
personal aspirations and how you want to evolve your org chart
for maximum future success. Your job as a manager is, after all,
to develop your team to continuously accomplish bigger goals, and
the right timing and approach to promotions can accelerate your
collective impact.

71% of employees believe that hiring from within is better for
scaling a business than hiring externally, according to a study
by Joblist. With your current team members having a much deeper
knowledge of your business than new hires, promoting tenured
employees into senior roles means less catch-up in
company-related areas, since they are building on their existing
experience.

That said, promotions must be handled carefully because they
affect team morale and employee retention. In fact, 50% of
workers said they would look for a new job if they donâ€™t receive
their expected promotion, per iCIMSâ€™ 2024 Workforce Report.

So, how do you make the right promotion decisions that will
position your team for long-term success?

Identify your big-picture goal

Now is a good time to evaluate, or re-evaluate, where you want
your department to be this year, and even over the next few
years. Consider documenting what you want to accomplish at these
stages and which resources you will need to put into place to
realize those goals. Be very specific about the types of outcomes
you want and what your ideal org chart might look like. As you do
this, think about which of your team members have the right
skills or potential to fill those roles. Remember to make this an
exploratory stage and donâ€™t come to any conclusions before you do
some deeper digging.

Understand desired growth paths

When planning how you want your team to evolve, itâ€™s very
important that you check in with each of your employees. Donâ€™t
assume you know how a particular team member sees their career
trajectory; ask them directly and try to remove any bias or
pressure to move in one way or the other. Do your best to find
out what drives them and what kind of work really excites them.
And remember that not all of your employees will want to or be
fit to evolve into managerial roles. So, make it clear that
growth can come in all forms and that meaningful career paths can
involve deepening skillsets or taking on larger projects over
time.

Set clear and measurable benchmarks

When you have career advancement discussions, be sure to set
clear goals for each employee to achieve before they move to the
next seniority level â€“ and discuss how each of those goals will
be measured and quantified. 86% of HR leaders believe that their
organizationsâ€™ career paths are unclear for employees, according
to Gartner, highlighting the existing gap when it comes to this
kind of clarity. For this reason, you need to be very consistent
about benchmarks to alleviate disparate expectations and feelings
of bias or resentment among team members. Find a way to
continuously track these goals, whether itâ€™s through work
management software or in specific employee documents reviewed in
your one-on-ones.

Seek several sources

Success metrics are definitely crucial for promotion intel, but
there are also soft skills, interpersonal relationships, and
other factors that should inform your decision-making. Be
proactive about discovering who is contributing the most to
projects. If youâ€™re seeing mentions of the same person in several
messaging threads or noticing someone always stepping in to help,
be sure to clock that information. Also, keep an eye out for
employees who are going above and beyond and showing a work ethic
that can be channeled and developed into leadership. Getting this
kind of information from all sides will help best inform your
approach to team growth and make absolutely sure youâ€™re promoting
the right people at the right time.

Recognize team impact

The challenging truth is that not everyone on the team will be
promoted, even when they might expect to be. Thatâ€™s why having
clear benchmarks and consistent expectations is key to minimizing
the negative feelings that may arise among those who are not
advanced during a particular cycle. Make sure you have a strong
communication plan in place and that before you announce the
promotions on your team, you reiterate your focus on key
benchmarks that dictate advancement. Remind your team that some
of their goals at their current level might still be in progress,
which is why itâ€™s natural for advancement to happen at different
stages for different people.

On a similar note, when handled the right way, seeing teammates
get promoted can actually spark motivation and build a sense of
trust in the process. It demonstrates that the system is fair and
based on clear, achievable criteria, encouraging everyone to stay
focused on their personal growth.

Water cooler chatter

JPMorgan disabled employee discussions amid
return-to-office backlash. The bank's internal memo last week
mandated all 300,000 employees to work full-time from the office
starting in March. After sharing the news on their internal
company website, JPMorgan was inundated with comments from
concerned employees addressing commuting costs, childcare issues,
and work-life balance concerns. As a result, the bank reportedly
swiftly shut down the comment functionality to silence further
group discussion.

â€œWe know that some of you prefer a hybrid
schedule and respectfully understand that not everyone will agree
with this decision.â€

- JP Morgan,  Memo

2024 was the hottest year weâ€™ve ever had. The
European Copernicus climate service, a main global data provider,
recently reported that last year was the first to pass the 1.5C
global warming limit, despite world leaders vowing a decade ago
they would work to avoid this.

â€œI think it's safe to say that both 2023 and
2024 temperatures surprised most climate scientists - we didn't
think we'd be seeing a year above 1.5C this early.â€

- Zeke Hausfather, Climatologist

Question of the week

Last weekâ€™s answer: Finland, where the
average worker drinks about 12 kg (26 lbs) of coffee per year-
equivalent to around 4 cups a day!

This weekâ€™s question: What percentage of professionals report
chronic exhaustion?

Just for laughs

â€œHave I said enough nice
things to move on to the negative feedback yet?â€

emails.subject: How The Warehouse Group saved ~52k dev hours with Docker
emails.content:
The Warehouse Group (The Group) is New Zealandâ€™s largest retail chain, employing more than 12,000 people and generating NZ$3.3 billion (US$2 billion) in annual revenue.

Adopting containerization saved The Group approximately 52,000 developer hours

The Group <https://em.docker.com/NzkwLVNTQi0zNzUAAAGXvK4DVMCxef5XgmCxcELh-dc6EJ1mlWoJkAMbK4ODnGxuT-smPjM1tFxPwZnOoYKwB1Qxghs=> previously struggled with traditional development practices involving long setup times, inconsistent environments, and slow deployment cycles. The Group adopted containerization technology for its ability to ensure uniform environments, eradicate deployment impediments, and enable developers to conduct local testing.

 Once they completed the second phase of their Golden Path initiative, which started in 2020, The Group reported an annualized saving of approximately 52,000 developer hours. As a result, the return on investment was realized in just eight months. Read the full case study <https://em.docker.com/NzkwLVNTQi0zNzUAAAGXvK4DVMCxef5XgmCxcELh-dc6EJ1mlWoJkAMbK4ODnGxuT-smPjM1tFxPwZnOoYKwB1Qxghs=> to learn how The Group was able to achieve these results with Docker.

emails.subject: Guide: Modernizing legacy applications with Docker
emails.content:
If your legacy systems are lagging behind swift technology advancements, youâ€™ll need a more agile and efficient solution to catch up. But transitioning to a modern framework is easier said than done. Thatâ€™s why Docker created a suite of tools to help you tackle this challenge efficiently.

 We've also created a guide to help you smoothly transition to a Docker-based environment. In the end, youâ€™ll have a fully transformed application using streamlined and future-proof systems.

Read more in our guide <https://em.docker.com/NzkwLVNTQi0zNzUAAAGW5FyBSwWiqt_0b9xMr67Yd8mQWieLakVz_XVEXsztGBR-k9IhSMZK0sPbK6BBGK8GtIv_dLg=> from Linux New Media to learn:



	- How to get started with containerizing legacy apps and set up a Docker development environment
	- A real-life use case of Dockerizing a legacy web server
	- How to network and enable isolated containers to communicate with each other and external networks for more control and security
	- How to leverage volumes to manage persistent data within Docker

emails.subject: Unlock AWS Free Tier: Live training series on Twitch
emails.content:
Training Live

AWS Free Tier:
Building Smart, Billing Less


Ready to dive into Amazon Web Services (AWS), but worried about unexpected costs? Join our 4-week live Twitch series, AWS Free Tier: Building Smart, Billing Less <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGWfO90qJrFHpjg3HYL1uBhgEcomNZLTciTqWNKR7pkwUH8hpooiTHrPFXLv6tYA7J49YJq_KU=>, starting November 1st. Every Friday, our expert hosts will guide you through AWS Free Tier services, teaching you to build projects while maintaining control over your billing.

You'll learn to navigate the AWS Console, use key services like Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) and Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3), and even explore Amazon Q Developer <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGWfO90qF83AwnRjCcW1fbQBD-FPT9ldLNplRRa-VT-tAHQu1UDiyjO68sqRU2nzEsP--ejAJo=> â€“ all free.

Join a community of learners, ask questions live, and complete a hands-on project.


View series details <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGWfO90qJrFHpjg3HYL1uBhgEcomNZLTciTqWNKR7pkwUH8hpooiTHrPFXLv6tYA7J49YJq_KU=>

Don't miss a thing. Effortlessly track changes to your data in Google  
Sheets.

Conditional notifications allow you to create custom rules in Sheets that  
send email alerts when certain criteria are met. When a specific edit is  
made, such as a task status change or a decrease in a key metric, you will  
receive an email with details about the change and who made the update. You  
can also configure the alerts for others by inputting their email addresses

	- Docker Engine â€“ manage your containers from the command line

emails.subject: Getting started with AWS Cost Anomaly Detection - chiragsrinivascybercellar (975050104657)
emails.content:
AWS Account: chiragsrinivascybercellar (975050104657)

Hello,

As part of your enablement of AWS Cost Explorer, we have configured AWS Cost Anomaly Detection for your account. Cost Anomaly Detection is a cost management service that helps you reduce cost surprises and enhance control without slowing innovation. It uses advanced machine learning models to detect and alert on anomalous spend patterns across your deployed AWS services. The cost monitor and daily email alert subscription we set up for you are free. You can change the default configuration via our console or API to customize the alerts you receive. You can also configure immediate alerts via SNS, though additional charges for using SNS may apply.

To get you started with AWS Cost Anomaly Detection, we pre-configured your account with an AWS Services monitor and a daily summary alerting subscription. With this setup, you will be alerted about anomalous spend that exceeds $100 and 40% of your expected spend across the majority of your AWS services in your accounts. See limitations here. If you want to modify your monitor or alert subscription setting, you can visit the Cost Anomaly Detection console or the public API to configure your cost monitors and alerting subscriptions to your specific needs. You can read more about how to use the service in our announcement blog, on our product page, and in our documentation.


FAQ:

Q: Why am I receiving this email?
In an effort to help our customers detect unintended spend, we are enabling Cost Anomaly Detection for all our new AWS Cost Explorer customers. This email is associated with your AWS account. If you are not interested in this service, you can opt-out by deleting your monitor and subscription in the console or via the API

Q: What is Cost Anomaly Detection?
Cost Anomaly Detection is an AWS cost management service that monitors customersâ€™ spend continuously, uses machine learning to detect anomalies, and generates alerts with root cause analysis of what caused the anomaly. With the service, you can reduce unplanned spend and minimize time and resources in triaging root causes. You can read more about the service on our product page and in our documentation.

Q: What is the pricing of Cost Anomaly Detection?
There is no charge for Cost Anomaly Detection. The cost monitor and daily email alert subscription we set up for you are free. You can change the default configuration via our console or API to customize the alerts you receive. You can also configure immediate alerts via SNS, though additional charges for using SNS may apply.

Q: What type of anomalies will Cost Anomaly Detection detect?
With the default setup, Cost Anomaly Detection will monitor costs on the majority of your AWS services in your accounts. See limitations here.

Q: How will I be alerted about anomalies?
Any anomalous spend related to your account(s) will show up in the Cost Anomaly Detection console and via the API. In addition, if the anomaly is above $100 and exceeds 40% of expected spend, you will receive a daily summary email to the primary email associated with your account, detailing the cost impact, account name, the name of the monitor, the start and end dates, and the service where it was observed. The email will also include potential root causes for the anomaly.

Q: How do I opt out?
If you are not interested in this service, you can opt-out by deleting your monitor(s) and subscription(s) in the console or via the API. Read more in our documentation.

Q: What happens if I opt out? Can I still enable Cost Anomaly Detection at a later date?
Yes, if you decide to opt out now, you will still be able to enable Cost Anomaly Detection at a later time. When you opt out, you will still be able to use Cost Explorer without Cost Anomaly Detection.


Questions?

If you have any questions regarding the information in this email or if you need additional assistance, please visit our FAQ or contact us at https://aws.amazon.com/support


Sincerely,
AWS Cost Management Team

emails.subject: Google Cloud Organization is now available for your domain
emails.content:
Google





We are happy to announce that the Cloud Organization is now available for  
your domain!

The Cloud Organization allows Google Cloud Platform admins to centrally  
manage all the Cloud Platform resources associated with their domain, apply  
IAM policies, consolidate Billing, and much more.

You can learn more about the Cloud Organization here and you can start  
using the Cloud Organization now by following the steps described in our  
Quickstart.

Thanks,
The Google Cloud Platform Team

emails.subject: Tips for using your new inbox
emails.content:
Tips for using your new inbox
[image: Gmail]

Welcome to your inbox
[image: Search]
Find emails fast
With the power of Google Search in your inbox, you can archive
<https://support.google.com/mail/answer/6576?hl=en-GB&utm_source=gmailwelcomeemail&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=gmailwelcome>
all your email and find it
<https://support.google.com/mail/answer/6593?hl=en-GB&utm_source=gmailwelcomeemail&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=gmailwelcome>
later in a flash. Your inbox stays tidy, and you never need to worry about
what to keep.
[image: Personalise]
Personalise cybercellar Mail
Customise inbox backgrounds, email signatures and other options in cybercellar
Mail settings
<https://support.google.com/mail/answer/6562?hl=en-GB&utm_source=gmailwelcomeemail&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=gmailwelcome>.
Review and adjust your privacy and security settings at My Account
<https://myaccount.google.com/>.
[image: Organise]
Organise your email
You can organise email with labels
<https://support.google.com/mail/answer/118708?hl=en-GB&utm_source=gmailwelcomeemail&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=gmailwelcome>,
which are like folders, but you can add more than one label to a message.
You can also use filters
<https://support.google.com/mail/answer/6579?hl=en-GB&utm_source=gmailwelcomeemail&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=gmailwelcome>
to automatically sort and categorise messages as they come in.
[image: Social]
Chat and meet directly from your inbox
Message with contacts in Google Chat
